---
description: Route relevant tasks to project skills automatically
alwaysApply: true
---

Skill Autoload Router:

When user request or target paths indicate docs impact workflow, load and apply skill:
- `.cursor/skills/feature-doc-impact/SKILL.md`

Trigger signals for `feature-doc-impact`:
- User asks to update/sync feature docs
- User asks whether docs need updates
- Work includes validation, Prisma schema, Server Actions, or dashboard/project/feature flow changes
- Target paths or edits include `docs/features/path-map.md` or `docs/features/index.md`

When user request or target paths indicate ManDev admin/settings change workflow, load and apply skill:
- `.cursor/skills/settings-change-checklist/SKILL.md`

Trigger signals for `settings-change-checklist`:
- User asks to fix/refactor project or feature forms, filters, or admin UI behavior
- User requests changes to dashboard shell, sidebar, theme, or toasts
- Target paths include `src/components/layout/`, `src/components/providers/`, `src/components/projects/`, `src/components/features/`, or Server Actions under `src/app/projects/` or `src/app/features/`

Conflict handling:
- If multiple workflows match, apply matching skills in this order:
  1) `feature-doc-impact`
  2) `settings-change-checklist`
- Keep architecture and safety rules as higher-priority guardrails.
